surgical procedures by mailed questionnaires.

Givon U(1), Ginsberg GM, Horoszowski H, Shemer J.

Author information:
(1)Sheba Medical Center.

A retrospective study comparing 700 consecutive total hip arthroplasties, 
utilizing four types of implants, was performed. Questionnaires based on hip 
scores were sent to 593 living patients. Useful responses were received from 363 
(61%) patients. Hip scores and quality-adjusted life-years were calculated. 
