Author information:
(1)Cell Biology Department, University of Calabria, Italy. 
g.debenedictis@unical.it

The possibility that four loci (REN, THO, PARP, SOD2) are associated with 
longevity was explored by comparing the genotypic pools of subjects older than 
100 years with those of younger subjects matched for sex and geographic area 
(northern and southern Italy). The markers (all located within the respective 
gene) were HUMREN4; HUMTHO1; HUMPARP (gt)845nt; SOD2(C/T)401nt. In order to 
reduce the number of genotypes, multiallelic polymorphisms were recoded as 
diallelic according to allele size and frequency patterns (small: S, and large: 
